<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>liable for something • liable to something</xh5><p> <i>liable for something—</i>legally responsible for smth.: Is a man <u>liable for</u> his wife’s debts in your country?</p><p><i>liable to something—</i>1. subject to some penalty: If you drive a car to the danger of the public, you make yourself <u>liable to</u> a heavy fine. 2. predisposed to smth.; likely to do smth.: We put ourselves under pressure, which made us <u>liable to</u> mistakes in making decisions.</p> </entry>
